      "id": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/06/260610003044.htm",
      "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/06/260610003044.htm",
      "title": "[ScienceDaily] Popular joint supplement glucosamine linked to faster Alzheimer’s progression",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/images/1920/senior-woman-taking-vitamin-supplement-medication-pill.webp\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nA major study suggests glucosamine, a popular supplement for joint pain, could be linked to faster progression from mild cognitive impairment to Alzheimer’s disease. Researchers found a 25% higher likelihood of developing dementia among glucosamine users and uncovered biological clues that may explain why.",
      "date_published": "2026-06-10T05:17:56+00:00",
      "authors": [
        {
          "name": "ScienceDaily",
          "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com"
        }
      ],
